sequenceDiagram
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS
    participant DSPO as DSPO Controller<br/>ServiceAccount token
    participant MariaDB as MariaDB<br/>3306/TCP MySQL
    participant S3 as S3 Object Store<br/>9000/TCP HTTP
    participant OCI as OCI Registry<br/>443/TCP HTTPS

    Note over K8sAPI,S3: Flow 1: DSPA Reconciliation
    K8sAPI->>DSPO: Watch DSPA CR change<br/>HTTPS/6443 TLS 1.2+<br/>ServiceAccount token
    DSPO->>MariaDB: Health check (SQL query)<br/>MySQL/3306 TLS configurable<br/>Password auth
    MariaDB-->>DSPO: Connection OK
    DSPO->>S3: Health check (StatObject)<br/>HTTP/9000 TLS configurable<br/>S3 access key
    S3-->>DSPO: Object OK
    DSPO->>K8sAPI: Apply rendered manifests<br/>HTTPS/6443 TLS 1.2+<br/>ServiceAccount token
    K8sAPI-->>DSPO: Resources created/updated

    Note over K8sAPI,S3: Flow 2: Pipeline API Server Request
    participant Client as Client<br/>(User/Dashboard)
    participant Route as OpenShift Route<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant RBAC as kube-rbac-proxy<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS
    participant API as ds-pipeline API Server<br/>8888/TCP HTTPS
    participant MLMD as MLMD gRPC<br/>8080/TCP gRPC

    Client->>Route: REST API call<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS<br/>Bearer token
    Route->>RBAC: Reencrypt TLS<br/>HTTPS/8443<br/>service-ca cert
    RBAC->>K8sAPI: SubjectAccessReview<br/>HTTPS/6443 TLS 1.2+<br/>Check DSPA/api permission
    K8sAPI-->>RBAC: Allowed/Denied
    RBAC->>API: Forward request<br/>HTTPS/8888 TLS (service-ca)<br/>PodToPodTLS
    API->>MariaDB: Query pipeline metadata<br/>MySQL/3306 TLS configurable<br/>Password
    MariaDB-->>API: Results
    API->>S3: Read/write artifacts<br/>HTTP/9000 TLS configurable<br/>S3 access key
    S3-->>API: Artifact data
    API->>MLMD: Store/retrieve metadata<br/>gRPC/8080 TLS (service-ca)<br/>PodToPodTLS
    MLMD-->>API: Metadata response
    API-->>RBAC: JSON response
    RBAC-->>Route: Response
    Route-->>Client: JSON response

    Note over DSPO,OCI: Flow 3: Managed Pipelines Init
    DSPO->>OCI: Pull managed-pipelines.json<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS 1.2+<br/>Pull secret keychain
    OCI-->>DSPO: Container image manifest
    Note over DSPO: Validate pipeline names<br/>against allowlist
    DSPO->>K8sAPI: Deploy init container<br/>with emptyDir mount
    Note over API: Init container writes<br/>pipelines to emptyDir<br/>API server reads at startup
